File: President Cyril Ramaphosa announced that the cumulative number of COVID-19 cases is now at 583 653, while the number of active cases is around 105 000. PRETORIA - President Cyril Ramaphosa said the reducing rate of COVID-19 infections is an encouraging sign but South Africans must maintain vigilance on Saturday evening. The president highlighted some of the recent encouraging signs in the country's battle against the coronavirus pandemic. COVID-19 in SA: Interpreting excess deaths Ramaphosa announced that the cumulative number of confirmed COVID-19 cases is now at 583 653, while the number of active cases is around 105 000. The president said fewer people are showing symptoms of the virus and fewer people have required hospitalisation for complications. He stated 11,667 people are confirmed to have died from COVID-19 in South Africa. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs. 